
Step 1: Identify calls passing explicit arrays to varargs methods, such as:

Java
foo(new String[]{"a", "b"})  // Where method is foo(String... args)
Step 2: Convert to direct varargs invocation:

Java
foo("a", "b")
Step 3: Preserve the original array-passing pattern when:

The array is constructed dynamically
The number of arguments isn't fixed at compile-time
